The paper presents a methodology for training recurrent neural networks from the Reservoir Computing family, which is a subfield of neural networks and falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the use of the proposed methodology in the context of applications such as wireless sensor networks and ambient intelligence, which are related to the fields of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of real-world data and discusses the impact of missing inputs on the performance of the model, which is related to the field of information theory (cs.IT).
